bc-vigil (0.5.5-1) stable; urgency=medium

  * UI: fix "page noire" symptom on /scans and /dedup/scans during a
    running scan. The auto-refresh used hx-target="body" hx-swap=
    "outerHTML", which momentarily blanked the document while the
    body element was being swapped. Switched to hx-target="this" /
    "main" with hx-select="table" / "main" so only the relevant
    fragment is replaced, preserving the rest of the page intact.
  * UI: nav menu labels disambiguated. "Cibles" / "Doublons" /
    "Analyses doublons" became "Cibles intégrité" / "Cibles doublons"
    / "Scans doublons" (FR), and "Targets" / "Dedup" / "Dedup scans"
    became "Integrity targets" / "Dedup targets" / "Dedup scans" (EN).
  * Config: BC_VIGIL_DISPLAY_TZ now defaults to detecting the system
    timezone (TZ env var, then /etc/timezone, then /etc/localtime
    symlink target, fallback UTC). Explicit BC_VIGIL_DISPLAY_TZ env
    still overrides.
  * Stale scan cleanup: emits an INFO log line at startup when one or
    more scans were marked failed by the cleanup pass.
  * Favicon: ships a small SVG favicon (no more 404 in browser
    devtools).
  * Packaging README: documents the systemd drop-in needed for dedup
    on paths outside /var/lib/bc-vigil (e.g. /storage on btrfs).

 -- Younes Benmoussa <younes.benmoussa@pm.me>  Tue, 21 Apr 2026 11:09:16 +0100

bc-vigil (0.5.4-1) stable; urgency=medium

  * Timezone: cron schedules are now evaluated and labelled in
    BC_VIGIL_DISPLAY_TZ rather than hard-coded UTC. Fixes the +1h
    offset between the time typed in the schedule form and the
    preview of next occurrences when display_tz is non-UTC.
    APScheduler and next_occurrences both honour the configured
    zone; invalid zone names fall back to UTC.
  * Schedule form: replaced <input type="time"> with a dedicated
    24h time picker (paired hour/minute <select> + hidden input).
    Guarantees 24h display regardless of browser locale (en-US
    browsers previously rendered AM/PM).
  * Stale scans cleanup: on service startup, scans left in
    pending/running by a previous (now-dead) bc-vigil process are
    auto-marked as failed with error "interrompu par un
    redémarrage du service". Only scans whose started_at precedes
    the current process start time are touched — in-flight scans
    of the running process are untouched.
  * Confirm labels (admin restore, admin reset, dedup delete):
    reworded from "Confirmation (taper <code>X</code>)" /
    "Confirm (type <code>X</code>)" to "Taper <code>X</code> pour
    confirmer" / "Type <code>X</code> to confirm" to avoid the
    awkward line-wrap around parentheses and <code> at narrow
    widths.

