bc-vigil (0.5.0-1) stable; urgency=medium

  * SQLite WAL mode enabled unconditionally (journal_mode=WAL,
    synchronous=NORMAL, busy_timeout=5000). Lets UI reads run
    concurrently with the big final write of duplicate groups,
    fixing the frozen-UI symptom on large scans (tested on 1M
    files / 150k groups). Backup now runs PRAGMA
    wal_checkpoint(TRUNCATE) first so the archived .sqlite is
    self-contained.
  * Duplicate groups persisted via executemany in chunks of 2000
    rows (was one SQLAlchemy session.add() per row). Drastically
    cuts the write-lock hold time at scan completion.
  * Index on dedup_groups(scan_id) and (scan_id, size) so the
    paginated scan detail view does not full-scan the table.
  * RssSampler interval raised from 50 ms to 200 ms (fewer
    syscalls on long scans, same peak precision).
  * Scan detail page paginated: 20 groups per page, sort by size
    descending by default. Summary header with total group count
    and current page. Warning banner above 10 000 groups
    recommending the auto-resolve rules over manual ticking.
  * Auto-resolve: four keep-rules apply to every group in the
    scan at once (shortest_path / oldest_mtime / newest_mtime /
    priority_folder). Opens the deletion preview with the
    pre-computed selection which the user still confirms with
    DELETE before any file is moved.
  * JS helpers on the scan detail form: "all but first" per
    group and for the whole visible page, "clear all".

 -- Younes Benmoussa <younes.benmoussa@pm.me>  Sun, 19 Apr 2026 19:30:00 +0000

bc-vigil (0.4.0-1) stable; urgency=medium

  * HDD/SSD/removable/network detection on dedup target creation
    via /proc/self/mountinfo and /sys/block/*/queue/rotational.
  * HDD detected -> threads forced to 1 (2-10x speedup reported
    vs multi-threaded reads on spinning rust); an advanced
    override checkbox keeps any user-specified value.
  * Network filesystem detected (NFS, SMB, SSHFS, 9p, ceph, AFS,
    gluster, rclone) -> target creation refused unless an opt-in
    checkbox is ticked, with a prominent warning on degraded
    performance.
  * Target detail page now shows the detected storage backend
    (SSD / HDD / removable / network / unknown) and the block
    device name.
  * Scan locking: trigger_scan raises ScanAlreadyRunningError if
    another PENDING/RUNNING scan exists for the same target.
    The run_scan route redirects silently to the active scan.
    Scheduled cron runs are skipped cleanly in that case.

 -- Younes Benmoussa <younes.benmoussa@pm.me>  Sun, 19 Apr 2026 19:00:00 +0000

bc-vigil (0.3.0-1) stable; urgency=medium

  * Dedup quarantine feature: select duplicate files in the scan
    detail view and move them to a reversible trash with full
    audit trail instead of deleting them outright.
  * New table DedupDeletion (scan_id, group_id, original_path,
    trash_path, size, hash, stored_mode, status, deleted_at,
    restored_at, purged_at, triggered_by, error).
  * Safety: re-hash with SHA256 at move-time to catch TOCTOU
    races; refuse symlinks / hardlinked-to-survivor / size drift
    / hash mismatch / missing source; minimum one survivor per
    group enforced; bulk threshold with explicit opt-in.
  * Storage: rename() atomic when same filesystem, fallback to
    copy2+fsync+unlink otherwise; warning shown for cross-FS
    items in the preview.
  * Restore button moves the file back to its original location
    (refused if a file now sits there); purge button deletes it
    for good.
  * Retention 7 days by default, configurable via
    BC_VIGIL_DEDUP_TRASH_RETENTION_DAYS; automatic purge job
    (APScheduler interval 24h). BC_VIGIL_DEDUP_TRASH_DIR to
    override the default <data_dir>/dedup/trash/ location (useful
    when duplicates sit on a different filesystem).
  * New /dedup/trash page with status filter and per-item
    restore/purge actions; sidebar entry with badge.
  * admin reset/restore now clear the trash directory when set
    separately from data_dir.

