bc-vigil (0.2.0-1) stable; urgency=medium

  * New dedup/ module: parallel duplicate-file finder backed by
    bc-duplicate. Mirrors integrity/: targets, schedules, scans,
    cancel (SIGTERM/SIGKILL), RSS sampling, APScheduler cron jobs,
    retention purge, CSV export of duplicate groups, FR/EN UI,
    sidebar entries "Doublons" and "Analyses doublons".
  * New tables DedupTarget, DedupSchedule, DedupScan, DedupGroup
    (all new columns nullable — _add_missing_columns stays
    compatible for in-place upgrades).
  * New settings: BC_VIGIL_BC_DUPLICATE_BINARY (default
    "bc-duplicate"), data_dir/dedup/ stores JSON reports.
  * admin_ops backup/restore/reset now cover dedup_dir and count
    dedup scans as active.
  * Recommends: bc-duplicate; postinst warns when missing.

 -- Younes Benmoussa <younes.benmoussa@pm.me>  Sun, 19 Apr 2026 17:00:00 +0000

bc-vigil (0.1.3-1) stable; urgency=medium

  * Fix scans permanently failing with "malformed left digest file"
    once an empty target was scanned: 0.1.1 synthesized a summary-only
    digest for empty targets, but bc-hash diff rejects that format,
    which broke every subsequent scheduled scan whose baseline was the
    synth file. run_hash no longer synthesizes; empty scans are stored
    with digest_path=NULL, and a baseline that is empty or unusable is
    automatically replaced by the first real scan (self-heal for prod
    DBs already poisoned by 0.1.1).

